stanzas.stanza_text:
But, as the Fruit alone commends the Tree,
So did Her Virtues praise her Piety,
Of which the Eldest-born was
And this the Needy to their Comfort knew;
For, while She liv'd, They Charitable grew;
Heav'n did but lend the Sums it might bestow,
And took Receits for all it did allow;
For still She Intrest paid to th' Poor below;
And if their number did increas'd appear,
Sometimes she from her private Wants wou'd spare,
And Trusted Heav'n was in Debt to Her.
